President Barack Obama issued a proclamation declaring June 14, 2014, as Flag Day and the week beginning June 8, 2014, as National Flag Week. The proclamation calls on all Americans to observe these days by displaying the American flag and to honor America's heritage. It also emphasizes the importance of the flag as a symbol of unity and the sacrifices made by those who have served in the military. The proclamation directs the display of the flag on all Federal Government buildings during that week and encourages public recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance.